sql:
SELECT state_fips, AVG(unemployment_rate) AS average_unemployment_rate
FROM unemployment_rates
GROUP BY state_fips;

SELECT SUM(num_unemployed) AS total_unemployed
FROM labor_force_data
WHERE year IN (2000, 2001);

external_knowledge:
Previous decade context: Referring to the year 2019 as the most recent year in the previous decade;
Unemployment rate average: Calculated by averaging the monthly or quarterly unemployment rates for the entire year;
Descending order of unemployment rates: The states are listed from the highest average unemployment rate to the lowest.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT state_fips) 
FROM labor_force_data 
WHERE num_unemployed > 0.5 * total_labor_force;
